Website: entwinement.co.nr

Written in java/processing(processing.org)


Features:
		2d shooter action
		customizable weapons
		create vehicles with xml files
		jython scripting engine
		
		

Controls:
		wasd movement
		lmb shoot
		rmb use attachment
		x pickup item, enter vehicle
		f throw weapon
		tab opens chat window
		
To Download:

First you must have git installed,
Then download with git clone git@github.com/whackashoe/Entwinement.git

Then please download the map/scenery/texture files from http://dl.dropbox.com/u/31011714/website/downloads/scentexmaps.zip. Unzip them and put them in your /Entwinement directory, you can copy your files from soldat into scenery and texture folders. For .PMS map files you need to copy them to /Entwinement/maps/data and then create maprepo .xml files in the /Entwinement/maps directory- you can just copy and paste an existing files maprepo and change the target to the new mao map.

You now need to download processing-1.51 so head on over to here: http://code.google.com/p/processing/downloads/list (make sure you get 1.51, the new alphas might not work).
 
Download http://dl.dropbox.com/u/31011714/website/downloads/libraries.zip and unzip them to your "sketchbook/libraries" folder, now start processing....

Load Entwinement.pde and then press play.

Woah- you made it, wasn't that hard was it?
